node.text:
When I met Paul and Helen in their New York showroom last year I could've listened to them talk about kitchens and design all day long. They create some of the most beautiful kitchens in the world and we cannot wait for you to see the homes they are working on. 

We wanted to share a glimpse into their showroom in England and the amazing work they do there. So excited for you to meet the @devolkitchens team on @magnolianetwork in 2021! #MagnoliaNetwork

node.text: We've been dreaming and planning and pouring our hearts into content for @magnolianetwork over the last year. Our network will launch in 2021, but we're so excited to share a preview of what we've been working on this coming January on @discoveryplus. You'll be able to watch the entire first season of my cooking show, new episodes of Fixer Upper: Welcome Home, and the first episodes of ten original series. This has been a labor of love, and we can't wait for you to watch—stay tuned! #MagnoliaNetwork (learn more at the link in profile)

There’s no one I'd rather eat an entire platter of sliders with after a dream of a week launching @magnolianetwork. Thank you all for celebrating with us this week!

To our amazingly talented & creative team that helped get us here—Thank YOU! 🙌🏽 We are so proud of you and forever grateful for all the hard work you have poured into this.

To all of the storytellers on this network—Thank you for trusting us to share your stories with the world, it is an absolute honor. ✨

We can't wait for you to see what all we’ve been working on the past couple of years. We’re adding new episodes every week and new series every month. You can check it all out on our new Magnolia app (or on @discoveryplus) using your discovery+ subscription!

node.text: Dreamers: Those who don’t just see the world for what it is, but for what it could be. Meet a few of @magnolianetwork’s dreamers on my story. #MagnoliaNetwork

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Joanna Stevens Gaines in Magnolia with @magnolia, @chipgaines, and @magnolianetwork. May be an image of 1 person, standing, outdoors and text that says 'A LITTLE SHOP ON BOSQUE -TiIE'.

node.text:
I had to drive by today because I was just feelin' all the feels. Never in a million years did I think this little shop we opened in 2003 called Magnolia would one day have the word "network" after it. I still can't fully take it all in, but I'm thankful for everything that led us to this point—both the small, simple moments and also the big, exciting and difficult ones. 

I really believe that dreams beget dreams. So whatever it is you’re dreaming about—whether it’s what to make for dinner or what business you're wanting to create—the world needs the passions and gifts you carry deep inside. 

So keep dreaming. And don't measure success by the size of a dream fulfilled. Base it on growth and the many things you learn along the way. 

I'm just so grateful to everyone who has had a hand in helping and supporting and loving us over the years. We are excited to share this dream of @MagnoliaNetwork with you this week—we really hope you love it. ❤️
